ANTHRAX - SPAIN (02): (EXTREMADURA) HORSE, HUMAN, SUSPECTED
***********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Tue 7 Sep 2021
Source: Europa Press [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.europapress.es/extremadura/noticia-detectado-caso-antrax-yegua-navalvillar-pela-20210907200205.html


The Ministry of Agriculture, Rural Development, Population and Territory has notified the Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food (MAPA) of a case of anthrax, which has affected a mare in the town of Navalvillar de Pela. In this case, the Junta de Extremadura is "in permanent contact" with the Ministry of Agriculture to deal with this matter, which is why it has launched an epidemiological surveillance plan and has made an emergency order to the Tragsatec company to carry out the monitoring of all incidents that may occur as a result of this case.

Likewise, the epidemiological surveys necessary to know the scope of the situation are being carried out, according to the Junta de Extremadura in a press release. As highlighted, this infection, caused by _Bacillus anthracis_, affects a large number of species, although it presents variable virulence and clinical symptoms.

